---
// _callouts-test.astro — Visual smoke page for the M2 T3 callout
// component library. Underscore-prefixed so Astro excludes it from
// the production build (per Astro's routing convention). Use:
//
//   npm run dev
//   curl http://localhost:4321/DSA/_callouts-test
//
// All 6 components rendered with sample content; auditor visually
// confirms each renders distinctly and the CodeBlock copy button
// fires.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Definition from '../components/callouts/Definition.astro';
import KeyIdea from '../components/callouts/KeyIdea.astro';
import Gotcha from '../components/callouts/Gotcha.astro';
import Example from '../components/callouts/Example.astro';
import Aside from '../components/callouts/Aside.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../components/callouts/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<Base title="cs-300 — callouts test">
  <h1>M2 T3 — Callout component smoke page</h1>

  <Definition title="Array">
    A variable that holds a fixed-length, ordered sequence of values, all of the
    same type, under a single name.
  </Definition>

  <KeyIdea title="Why direct access is O(1)">
    Array elements are stored contiguously; element address = start + i × size.
  </KeyIdea>

  <Gotcha title="Off-by-one errors">
    A four-element array has valid indices 0..3, not 1..4.
  </Gotcha>

  <Example title="C++ sequence containers">
    <p>Three idiomatic choices for a fixed-element-count list:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>std::array&lt;T, N&gt;</code> — size known at compile time</li>
      <li><code>std::vector&lt;T&gt;</code> — dynamic, contiguous, default choice</li>
      <li><code>std::list&lt;T&gt;</code> — doubly-linked, O(1) splice/erase</li>
    </ul>
  </Example>

  <Aside title="The model has a name: Word-RAM">
    The picture used above has a formal name in algorithm analysis: the Word-RAM
    model. Chapter 3 adopts this language when it makes Big-O analysis precise.
  </Aside>

  <h2>CodeBlock — prop form</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    lang="cpp"
    code={`#include <vector>

int main() {
  std::vector<int> v;
  v.resize(3);   // v is now {0, 0, 0}
  return 0;
}`}
  />

  <h2>CodeBlock — slot form</h2>
  <CodeBlock lang="cpp">{`auto sum(const std::vector<int>& xs) {
  long long s = 0;
  for (int x : xs) s += x;
  return s;
}`}</CodeBlock>
</Base>
